# Testing Standards

## Test Structure

- Follow the **Arrange–Act–Assert** pattern: set up state, perform the action, assert the outcome.
- Use descriptive test names that express intent: `it("returns null when element has no children")`, not `it("works")`.
- Group related tests in `describe` blocks named after the unit under test.
- Keep each `it` block focused on a single behavior — one logical assertion per test (multiple `expect` calls are fine if they all verify the same behavior).

## What to Test

- Test public interfaces, not implementation details — if you have to access private members, reconsider the design.
- Unit-test pure functions in `packages/math`, `packages/common`, and `packages/utils` exhaustively.
- Integration-test React components with `@testing-library/react` — interact via accessible queries (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`).
- Do not write tests that only verify that a mock was called with specific arguments — test observable side effects instead.

## Mocking

- Mock only external I/O (network, localStorage, canvas API) — do not mock modules in the same package unless absolutely necessary.
- Use `vi.spyOn` for partial mocks; use `vi.mock` for full module replacement (document the reason).
- Reset all mocks in `afterEach` to prevent state leakage between tests.

## Coverage Targets (vitest.config.mts thresholds)

| Metric | Minimum |
|---|---|
| Lines | 60% |
| Branches | 70% |
| Functions | 63% |
| Statements | 60% |

Do not decrease these thresholds when adding new code.

## Performance

- Avoid `setTimeout` / `waitFor` with magic delays — use `waitFor` with condition predicates.
- Tests must complete in < 5 s individually; flag tests exceeding this as slow and optimize.

## How to Verify

1. Run `yarn test:app --watch=false` — all tests must pass.
2. Run `yarn test:coverage` — confirm coverage thresholds are met (check `v8` output table).
3. Run `yarn test:typecheck` — test files must also pass TypeScript checks.
4. Search for skipped tests before merging: `grep -rn "\.skip\|xit\|xdescribe" --include="*.test.*"` — all skips must have a linked issue comment.
